                    {
                        "subSectionTitle": "ideate",
                        "subSectionTitleType": "level2",
                        "subSectionData": [
                            {
                                "type": "DESCRIPTION",
                                "data": {
                                    "text": [
                                        "The first step was to identify a message behind the brand. I wanted Silverpoint to lean heavily towards traditional with a contemporary twist.",
                                        "I wanted the wordmark to reflect the high quality of the product inside — as such, I looked I looked for typefaces that reminded me of traditional luxury in art. I chose a few typefaces to start my exploration that were either reminiscent of typefaces seen on Roman statue inscriptions, or luxurious, heavy-weighted serifs.",
                                        "I focused on two different design directions, making a different wordmark and business card for each one.",
                                        "For the secondary typeface on the business cards, I wanted to choose a serif font that was delicate but still had a medium contrast: FreightText Pro."
                                    ]
                                }
                            },
                            {
